# TDD Development

Follow **Red → Green → Refactor**. Every feature has tests; tests follow the Contraponto pattern (JUnit + Selenium, no Cucumber).

## Mandatory Rules

1. **Every feature has tests** — no production feature without a matching JUnit test class.
2. **Test layers** — pick the right annotation:
   - `@UnitTest` — pure domain/service logic, no Quarkus boot
   - `@QuarkusIntegrationTest` — REST Assured / CDI / MongoDB
   - `@WebPlatformTest` / `@WebEditorTest` — browser tests via `App` DSL (never raw Selenium in test methods)
3. **Never raw Selenium in test methods** — extend interactions through `App` inner page classes.
4. **Data setup** — use `Given.persistProject()` / `Given.cleanup()`; fixed times via `TestTimes`.

Do not merge unrelated behaviors into one test method. Do not implement behavior without a failing test first.

## Layout

```
src/test/java/dev/vepo/youtube/creator/
├── shared/           ← @WebTest, App, Given, WebTestExtension, TestTags
├── project/          ← domain + persistence tests
├── model/            ← timeline model tests
├── service/          ← MLT and render tests
├── api/              ← REST endpoint tests (@QuarkusIntegrationTest)
└── web/              ← Selenium (@WebPlatformTest, @WebEditorTest) + REST (@QuarkusIntegrationTest)
```

## Test Class Template

```java
@WebEditorTest
class MyFeatureTest {

    @BeforeEach
    void setUp() {
        Given.cleanup();
    }

    @Test
    void scenario_description(App app) {
        app.access()
           .openNewProject()
           .assertEditorLoaded();
    }
}
```

## Verification

```bash
./mvnw test                           # all tests
./mvnw test -Ptest-unit               # fast domain tests
./mvnw test -Ptest-quarkus            # integration (needs MongoDB)
GITHUB_ACTIONS=true ./mvnw test -Ptest-web   # browser (needs Chrome)
```

All tests must pass before marking work complete.
